      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e3778"> </a>Changing the headlight bulbs
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3781"> </a>Before replacing a burnt out bulb, ensure that the replacement bulb has the same voltage and power rating as specified for
            the concerned lighting device (<a href="50528.html#DUC886ba7d0296a100587d5e8e482a98fd2">Lights/Instruments</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/warning.jpg">Warning
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3787"> </a>The halogen light bulbs in the headlight become hot when switched on and remain hot for some time after they are switched
         off. Allow bulbs to cool before replacing them.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3790"> </a>Following is the position of the lights in the headlight:
         </div>
      </div>
