      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3818"> </a>The two spot lights (4) are located outside the front headlight.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_002804103.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3824"> </a>Remove the panel as described in Section "<a href="77975.html#DUCc08298b82a73100585b0e07f17a720d2">Removing the panel</a>".
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3830"> </a>High beam (3).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3832"> </a>To reach the high beams (3) completely turn the handlebar and disconnect connectors (5) located inside the high beams.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_015804218.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3837"> </a>Turn high beams (3) counter-clock wise, remove them from theirs seat and replace the burnt out bulbs.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_003004105.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3842"> </a>Do not touch the transparent part of the new bulb with the hands. This would cause it to blacken thereby reducing bulb brilliancy.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3845"> </a>Refit the previously removed components.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e3848"> </a>Changing the turn indicator light bulbs
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3851"> </a>It is only possible to replace the rear turn indicator bulbs.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3853"> </a>Undo the screw (1) and detach the lens (2) from the turn indicator support (3).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3855"> </a>If it proves necessary to remove support (3), refer to Section "<a href="81760.html#DUC5d46b8202b9e100589cff710a060a8d2">Removing the number plate holder</a>".
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3860"> </a>Fit the spare bulb by removing it and then pressing and turning it clockwise until it clicks into its seat.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3862"> </a>Refit the lens by inserting the tab (A) in the corresponding slot in the turn indicator support.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3864"> </a>Tighten the screw (4).
         </div>
      </div>
